<i>Could it be?!</i>

126
00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:56.190
<i>It very well could be!</i>

127
00:06:59.430 --> 00:07:01.680
Alcohol Soft!

128
00:07:02.060 --> 00:07:03.600
I did it!

129
00:07:03.600 --> 00:07:06.290
I traveled back in time again!

130
00:07:09.240 --> 00:07:10.820
No way in hell!

131
00:07:12.870 --> 00:07:14.610
Start Today
Intro to Personal Computers
Learn Windows 95

132
00:07:13.170 --> 00:07:14.610
Magazines?

133
00:07:14.610 --> 00:07:16.520
I'm done with this place!

134
00:07:24.650 --> 00:07:26.240
Mamoru-kun?

135
00:07:26.890 --> 00:07:28.820
You're Mamoru-kun, right?!

136
00:07:28.820 --> 00:07:30.220
It's me, Konoha!

137
00:07:33.470 --> 00:07:35.730
Hey! Mamoru-kun!

138
00:07:35.730 --> 00:07:36.990
Mamoru-kun!

139
00:07:36.990 --> 00:07:38.040
Mamocchi!

140
00:07:38.040 --> 00:07:39.960
Meiko-san! Kaori-san!

141
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:40.380
What?

142
00:07:41.410 --> 00:07:43.020
Kono-chan?!

143
00:07:43.020 --> 00:07:45.070
I've missed you so much!

144
00:07:46.510 --> 00:07:48.020
Kono-chan!

145
00:07:48.020 --> 00:07:49.720
Why are you soaking wet?

146
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:55.330
Who was she, again?

147
00:07:55.330 --> 00:07:56.790
It's Kono-chan!

148
00:07:56.790 --> 00:07:58.760
The part-timer from a long time ago!

149
00:07:58.760 --> 00:08:00.710
Oh, I remember now.

150
00:08:00.710 --> 00:08:03.180
The girl who called herself a time traveler.

151
00:08:03.180 --> 00:08:04.420
She was still alive?

152
00:08:04.830 --> 00:08:07.410
Why did you suddenly disappear?

153
00:08:07.830 --> 00:08:08.990
That's right.

154
00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:10.870
We didn't even get a chance to pay you.

155
00:08:10.870 --> 00:08:12.690
We were worried sick about you!

156
00:08:13.110 --> 00:08:16.790
I didn't know how to get here,

157
00:08:16.790 --> 00:08:19.010
but I finally made it back!

158
00:08:19.010 --> 00:08:19.920
What?

159
00:08:19.920 --> 00:08:22.770
Are you saying you lost directions
 to this place for four years?

160
00:08:22.770 --> 00:08:24.660
You've gotta be kidding!

161
00:08:25.950 --> 00:08:29.430
We would have come and found 
you if you'd called us.

162
00:08:28.040 --> 00:08:29.430
<i>Four years later...</i>

163
00:08:29.770 --> 00:08:30.760
Um!

164
00:08:31.330 --> 00:08:33.100
I know this is sudden,

165
00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:36.070
but please let me work here again!

166
00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:37.490
What?!

167
00:08:37.490 --> 00:08:41.230
I want to make games at this company!

168
00:08:41.660 --> 00:08:45.190
That really did come out of nowhere.

169
00:08:45.190 --> 00:08:48.540
You went missing for four years, and 
now you want to work with us again?

170
00:08:48.540 --> 00:08:49.640
But, but...

171
00:08:49.640 --> 00:08:51.850
I wanted to work here again!

172
00:08:51.850 --> 00:08:54.710
I've been trying all this 
time to come back here!

173
00:08:54.710 --> 00:08:56.920
All this time, for four years?

174
00:08:57.540 --> 00:09:02.090
Well, you say four years, but it was 
really more like a week or so...

175
00:09:02.090 --> 00:09:03.680
Um...

176
00:09:05.090 --> 00:09:06.160
Don't do it.

177
00:09:06.160 --> 00:09:08.200
We should kick her to the curb, pronto.

178
00:09:08.630 --> 00:09:11.910
Yeah, she's only become more of a menace.

179
00:09:13.550 --> 00:09:15.100
Listen to me, Kono-chan.

180
00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:19.810
The environment we're working in has 
changed a lot since you were here.

181
00:09:19.810 --> 00:09:20.950
Environment?

182
00:09:20.950 --> 00:09:21.540
Yeah.

183
00:09:21.540 --> 00:09:25.860
The next Alcohol Soft game is 
going to be made for Windows.

184
00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:27.720
What? Windows?!

185
00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:29.620
You've heard of it, haven't you?

186
00:09:29.620 --> 00:09:31.360
It's selling like hotcakes now,

187
00:09:31.360 --> 00:09:36.670
so we're thinking of making our next game 
on Windows instead of just for the PC-98.

188
00:09:36.670 --> 00:09:39.040
The way we paint CGs and 
all has changed, too.

189
00:09:39.040 --> 00:09:43.030
I-I know <i>all</i> about Windows!

190
00:09:43.030 --> 00:09:45.180
I use Win10 everyday!

191
00:09:45.540 --> 00:09:47.440
Win10?

192
00:09:47.910 --> 00:09:52.010
Looks like the times have 
finally caught up with me!

193
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:54.850
Behold!

194
00:09:54.850 --> 00:09:57.280
My drawings that I made in Photoshop!

195
00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:14.350
I-It won't turn on!

196
00:10:14.350 --> 00:10:16.020
Because I fell into the pool?!

197
00:10:16.020 --> 00:10:17.760
No way!

198
00:10:17.760 --> 00:10:19.990
Kick her out! Kick her out!

199
00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:23.870
Okay, Kono-chan.

200
00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:27.530
Can I ask you to act as 
detective for Mamocchi?

201
00:10:28.410 --> 00:10:29.670
Detective?

202
00:10:30.010 --> 00:10:32.180
Hey! You're hiring her?!

203
00:10:32.180 --> 00:10:38.120
By "detective," I mean someone to bring 
troublesome employees back to the office.

204
00:10:38.120 --> 00:10:41.400
Please find Mamocchi and 
bring him back here!

205
00:10:41.400 --> 00:10:42.770
What?!

206
00:10:43.020 --> 00:10:46.480
You see, the development of our 
game is currently on hold.

207
00:10:46.480 --> 00:10:50.350
Mamoru-kun says he doesn't want 
to make games on Windows.

208
00:10:50.350 --> 00:10:53.290
He said he'll quit unless 
it's a PC-98 exclusive.

209
00:10:53.620 --> 00:10:57.180
Mamocchi's the only programmer we have.

210
00:10:57.180 --> 00:10:59.990
Without him, we can't make any games.

211
00:11:00.550 --> 00:11:01.880
<i>Grr...</i>

212
00:11:01.880 --> 00:11:03.820
<i>They're sticking me with the chores again!</i>

213
00:11:03.820 --> 00:11:06.710
<i>Why am I stuck in this 
loop of part-time work?!</i>

214
00:11:06.710 --> 00:11:10.310
<i>But without Mamoru-kun here, 
there won't be any game dev to speak of!</i>

215
00:11:11.800 --> 00:11:14.950
I'll take up the mantle of 
detective for Mamoru-kun!

216
00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:18.320
Super cop Konoha is on the case!

217
00:11:20.260 --> 00:11:22.580
She really is a menace...

218
00:11:22.570 --> 00:11:24.330
Personal Computer Shop "R"

219
00:11:22.580 --> 00:11:25.800
I'll have him back here in a sec!

220
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:27.120
Personal Computer Shop "R"

221
00:11:27.690 --> 00:11:30.790
Kao-san, you're bringing her on?

222
00:11:30.790 --> 00:11:34.420
Just like last time, I can't 
say no to that energy of hers.

223
00:11:34.420 --> 00:11:35.830
She hasn't changed a bit.

224
00:11:35.830 --> 00:11:39.350
I wonder what she was up to 
these past four years...

225
00:11:41.890 --> 00:11:46.170
That was PUFFY's hit single, "True Asia."

226
00:11:46.590 --> 00:11:51.370
They say, "Wear your finest sandals 
in search of an older wife."

227
00:11:51.370 --> 00:11:55.360
I'm still looking for a 
marriage partner in sandals!

228
00:12:00.650 --> 00:12:01.850
So hot...

229
00:12:01.850 --> 00:12:04.250
<i>Alcohol Soft?</i>

230
00:12:04.250 --> 00:12:07.770
<i>Ah, I seem to remember an 
old brand with that name.</i>

231
00:12:07.770 --> 00:12:09.760
<i>I can't imagine they still exist.</i>

232
00:12:09.760 --> 00:12:13.770
<i>Is the reason because Mamoru-kun 
ended up quitting?</i>

233
00:12:14.030 --> 00:12:15.690
Mamoru-kun!

234
00:12:15.690 --> 00:12:17.960
Where are you?!

235
00:12:17.960 --> 00:12:19.840
Messe Sanoh

236
00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:22.840
Messe Sanoh

237
