H-How do I put it...

259
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:33.620
You seem like you're used to 
buying those kinds of games.

260
00:13:33.660 --> 00:13:36.580
You seem like you're used to buying those kinds of games

261
00:13:37.520 --> 00:13:41.300
Do I really look like
I buy eroge all the time?

262
00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:42.790
E-Ero...

263
00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:42.800
Ero Ero Ero

264
00:13:42.790 --> 00:13:45.070
Th-Th-Th-That's not what I meant!

265
00:13:45.070 --> 00:13:48.430
You just looked so confident, 
even in a place like this.

266
00:13:48.430 --> 00:13:49.910
A place like this?

267
00:13:49.910 --> 00:13:51.540
You mean a video game store?

268
00:13:52.430 --> 00:13:56.030
C'mon, it's not any kind of 
seedy shop or anything...

269
00:13:56.030 --> 00:13:58.350
Wait, are you under the age of 18?

270
00:13:58.350 --> 00:14:00.850
Oh, no, I'm 19!

271
00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:03.020
There's no issue with my age!

272
00:14:03.020 --> 00:14:07.460
I just can't work up the 
courage to enter the store...

273
00:14:07.780 --> 00:14:10.990
<i>Then you should just go 
on Amazon or Getchu...</i>

274
00:14:10.990 --> 00:14:14.230
<i>Wait, those don't exist yet!</i>

275
00:14:17.590 --> 00:14:19.490
<i>Wh-What do I do?</i>

276
00:14:19.490 --> 00:14:21.720
<i>I should be looking for Mamoru-kun...</i>

277
00:14:22.260 --> 00:14:23.820
<i>Still...</i>

278
00:14:25.890 --> 00:14:27.080
Sure thing!

279
00:14:28.150 --> 00:14:30.220
Let's go in together!

280
00:14:31.510 --> 00:14:33.070
Y-Yes!

281
00:14:33.070 --> 00:14:34.460
Okay, off we go.

282
00:14:34.460 --> 00:14:35.510
U-Um...

283
00:14:36.780 --> 00:14:39.400
My name is Toya Yamada.

284
00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:41.350
N-Nice to meet you!

285
00:14:41.350 --> 00:14:44.470
Oh yeah, I forgot to introduce myself!

286
00:14:44.470 --> 00:14:46.910
I'm Konoha Akisato!

287
00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:48.080
You'll be fine!

288
00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:49.890
There's nothing scary about eroge!

289
00:14:56.480 --> 00:15:00.620
<i>I've actually never been 
inside Messe Sanoh, either!</i>

290
00:15:00.620 --> 00:15:02.740
<i>My first time at Sanoh!</i>

291
00:15:04.200 --> 00:15:05.930
<i>She's shaking in fear!</i>

292
00:15:05.930 --> 00:15:07.660
<i>That's adorable!</i>

293
00:15:07.660 --> 00:15:11.130
<i>A reward event this juicy 
is rare even for eroge!</i>

294
00:15:11.130 --> 00:15:13.680
Look, they've got lots of games for sale!

295
00:15:14.810 --> 00:15:17.560
Doukyuusei 2 - Kakyuusei - Isaku
Welcome to Pia Carrot!! - Kizuato

296
00:15:19.320 --> 00:15:20.730
Oh, they have them!

297
00:15:20.730 --> 00:15:22.390
<i>Pia Carrot</i> and <i>Kizuato</i>!

298
00:15:32.230 --> 00:15:33.990
You got them!

299
00:15:33.990 --> 00:15:34.620
Yes!

300
00:15:34.990 --> 00:15:36.540
I'm so glad.

301
00:15:36.540 --> 00:15:38.800
I read about these two 
games on the NIFTY forums,

302
00:15:38.800 --> 00:15:40.380
and I really wanted to play them!

303
00:15:40.380 --> 00:15:41.630
Good for you!

304
00:15:42.180 --> 00:15:44.190
Th-Thank you very much!

305
00:15:44.190 --> 00:15:45.480
It's fine, it's fine!

306
00:15:45.480 --> 00:15:46.290
Don't worry about it!

307
00:15:46.290 --> 00:15:49.180
Do you come to Akihabara often?

308
00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:51.010
Ah, yeah.

309
00:15:51.010 --> 00:15:53.620
I'm always here, I guess?

310
00:15:54.730 --> 00:15:56.480
Oh, yeah!

311
00:15:56.480 --> 00:15:58.230
I should really get going!

312
00:15:58.230 --> 00:16:00.100
Well, enjoy your games!

313
00:16:00.100 --> 00:16:01.530
Bye-bye!

314
00:16:06.550 --> 00:16:09.360
Man, she sure was a cutie.

315
00:16:09.360 --> 00:16:14.250
I guess in this era, you didn't find 
a lot of girls in those kinds of stores.

316
00:16:17.240 --> 00:16:19.120
Ah! Mamoru-kun!

317
00:16:21.700 --> 00:16:22.660
Stare.

318
00:16:24.050 --> 00:16:25.740
Suspect in sight.

319
00:16:26.980 --> 00:16:30.160
<i>Mamoru sure has grown up.</i>

320
00:16:30.570 --> 00:16:33.990
<i>Last time I met him, he was 15.</i>

321
00:16:34.440 --> 00:16:37.870
<i>So now he's... 19?!</i>

322
00:16:38.360 --> 00:16:40.230
<i>We're the same age now!</i>

323
00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:44.380
Look at you all, real fine and handsome...

324
00:16:44.380 --> 00:16:46.400
Oh! What a find!

325
00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:48.390
A 98 VM!

326
00:16:48.390 --> 00:16:51.610
You must have worked real hard...

327
00:16:52.090 --> 00:16:57.450
<i>Mamoru-kun's talking to the used PCs 
with such kindness in his eyes...</i>

328
00:16:57.450 --> 00:16:59.480
<i>What a creepy kid.</i>

329
00:17:00.160 --> 00:17:03.320
<i>I hate to interrupt him 
in the middle of this...</i>

330
00:17:03.320 --> 00:17:06.250
Mamoru-kun, you're under arrest!

331
00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:09.030
J-Just kidding...

332
00:17:09.690 --> 00:17:11.540
Mamoru-kun, it's been a while!

333
00:17:11.540 --> 00:17:13.430
You still remember me, don't you?

334
00:17:13.870 --> 00:17:15.210
I've never seen you in my life.

335
00:17:15.210 --> 00:17:16.360
What?!

336
00:17:16.360 --> 00:17:18.450
Didn't we make a game together?!

337
00:17:18.450 --> 00:17:21.900
I've never had so much fun 
making a game before!

338
00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:25.230
I don't want to remember any of 
the games we made in the past.

339
00:17:25.230 --> 00:17:26.350
Uguu...

340
00:17:26.350 --> 00:17:29.100
I-I guess you don't remember it as fondly...

341
00:17:29.100 --> 00:17:31.720
So much for that enthusiasm of yours...

342
00:17:31.720 --> 00:17:33.180
Disappearing on us like that...

343
00:17:36.410 --> 00:17:37.330
Eh?

344
00:17:38.670 --> 00:17:40.660
Do you think she'll bring him back?

345
00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:41.570
Huh?

346
00:17:41.570 --> 00:17:44.810
Oh, you mean Kono-chan and Mamoru-kun?

347
00:17:44.810 --> 00:17:45.880
That's right.

348
00:17:47.110 --> 00:17:51.090
Mamoru-kun's passion for the 
PC-98 is the real deal.

349
00:17:51.090 --> 00:17:56.010
But if she doesn't bring him back, 
we can't transition over to Windows.

350
00:17:56.010 --> 00:17:59.130
We can just hire someone else.

351
00:17:59.130 --> 00:18:01.090
Just because he's the manager's son,

352
00:18:01.090 --> 00:18:03.970
we're the ones who have been 
relying on him all this time.

353
00:18:04.300 --> 00:18:05.890
That may be true...

354
00:18:07.610 --> 00:18:11.120
but I know that Kono-chan 
will bring him back!

355
00:18:09.150 --> 00:18:15.110
Computer Workshop     Tanaka

356
00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:15.120
M-Mamoru-kun!

357
00:18:15.120 --> 00:18:17.170
Mamoru-kun, let's go back!

358
00:18:18.790 --> 00:18:22.480
I don't know how long I can stay here.

359
00:18:22.480 --> 00:18:25.790
So I wanna go back soon and make some games!

360
00:18:26.420 --> 00:18:28.950
Just how demanding can you be?!

361
00:18:28.950 --> 00:18:32.630
Why do I have to make games for <i>your</i> sake?!

362
00:18:34.200 --> 00:18:36.520
I won't develop any games for Windows.

363
00:18:36.970 --> 00:18:39.570
I only make games for the PC-98.

364
00:18:39.570 --> 00:18:41.350
Go find someone else.

365
00:18:41.350 --> 00:18:45.020
Does it really matter that much 
whether it's PC-98 or Windows?!

366
00:18:48.410 --> 00:18:50.040
Come over here for a minute!

367
00:18:53.540 --> 00:18:54.670
Pop quiz.

368
00:18:54.670 --> 00:18:55.730
What?!

369
00:18:55.730 --> 00:18:59.440
Explain what all of these rear 
ports are, one by one.

370
00:18:59.440 --> 00:19:00.740
What?!

371
00:19:00.740 --> 00:19:02.740
If you get everything right, I'll go back.

372
00:19:04.310 --> 00:19:06.390
Um...

373
00:19:06.390 --> 00:19:08.670
Th-That one's a power plug!

374
00:19:08.670 --> 00:19:10.660
Anyone could figure that one out.

375
00:19:10.660 --> 00:19:12.420
Th-Then there's...

376
00:19:12.420 --> 00:19:14.840
Um, um...

377
00:19:16.400 --> 00:19:19.230
Wh-Who cares if I don't know what they are?!

378
00:19:19.230 --> 00:19:21.840
I can draw pictures just fine either way!

379
00:19:22.740 --> 00:19:24.230
That's what they all say.

380
00:19:24.230 --> 00:19:28.670
We live in a time where the people buying 
computers don't know anything about them.

381
00:19:28.670 --> 00:19:32.090
And what's more, it's people 
like them who are making games!

382
00:19:32.090 --> 00:19:33.450
It's so messed up!

383
00:19:33.450 --> 00:19:34.580
Listen up.

384
00:19:34.580 --> 00:19:36.940
Programming is about 
tinkering with machines!

385
00:19:36.940 --> 00:19:38.950
It's a conversation with the machine!

386
00:19:39.180 --> 00:19:41.970
Hey there, 98 VM-kun!

387
00:19:41.970 --> 00:19:44.610
Can you run this program for me?

388
00:19:44.610 --> 00:19:47.650
Your 256KB of memory 
ought to be enough, right?

389
00:19:47.650 --> 00:19:49.690
There, you managed it!

390
00:19:49.690 --> 00:19:51.670
You did a great job!

391
00:19:51.670 --> 00:19:54.500
I-I can't stop shivering, Mamoru-kun.

392
00:19:55.010 --> 00:19:57.000
This is what programming is.

393
00:19:57.340 --> 00:20:01.260
But now there's this thing called 
Windows trying to butt in.

394
00:20:01.620 --> 00:20:05.480
That means you can't talk 
directly to the PC-98 anymore!

395
00:20:05.480 --> 00:20:08.460
B-But Windows is so convenient!

396
00:20:08.460 --> 00:20:10.750
I don't know how to use 
anything other than Windows!

397
00:20:10.750 --> 00:20:13.700
That's why you don't understand 
how computers work!

398
00:20:13.940 --> 00:20:16.480
Kaori and Meiko are going 
to follow suit, right?

399
00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:18.200
Help yourselves!

400
00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:19.770
I've had enough!

401
00:20:20.240 --> 00:20:22.800
It's PC-98 or nothing for me!

402
00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:31.890
Mamoru-kun...

403
00:20:31.890 --> 00:20:32.960
What now?

404
00:20:33.980 --> 00:20:34.870
That...

405
00:20:35.510 --> 00:20:36.500
What?!

406
00:20:36.500 --> 00:20:37.540
That's great!

407
00:20:37.540 --> 00:20:38.620
Huh?

408
00:20:38.620 --> 00:20:40.500
I think that's really great, Mamoru-kun!

409
00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:41.950
You're the best!

410
00:20:41.950 --> 00:20:44.290
You love the PC-98 so much!

411
00:20:44.520 --> 00:20:48.890
I've never met anyone who was so 
passionate about making games!

412
00:20:48.890 --> 00:20:52.820
No, everyone else at 
Alcohol Soft is the same!

413
00:20:52.820 --> 00:20:55.440
No one at my company ever says anything...

414
00:20:55.440 --> 00:20:58.060
None of them would ever argue like this.

415
00:20:58.290 --> 00:21:01.060
That's why I wanted to come back here!

416
00:21:01.060 --> 00:21:03.780
I wanted to see all of you again!

417
00:21:08.540 --> 00:21:10.650
What are you saying?

418
00:21:10.650 --> 00:21:13.850
I was assigned as a detective for you!

419
00:21:13.850 --> 00:21:16.710
I promised them I'd bring you back!

420
00:21:17.190 --> 00:21:19.660
I'll do it if they make 
it a PC-98 exclusive.

421
00:21:19.660 --> 00:21:21.400
Other than that, not a chance.

422
00:21:21.400 --> 00:21:22.590
That's all there is to it.

423
00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:25.250
Mamoru-kun!

424
00:21:25.810 --> 00:21:29.340
Are you really a time traveler?

425
00:21:29.340 --> 00:21:30.020
What?

426
00:21:30.380 --> 00:21:32.910
Of course I don't actually 
believe you are one.

427
00:21:33.450 --> 00:21:35.270
But if it's true...

428
00:21:36.470 --> 00:21:37.940
Don't you dare do anything.

429
00:21:40.380 --> 00:21:44.150
Time travelers aren't supposed 
to change history, right?

430
00:21:44.960 --> 00:21:48.030
In that case, don't interfere 
with what I do, either.

431
00:21:59.150 --> 00:22:01.180
I'll make sure I capture you!

432
00:22:01.390 --> 00:22:03.530
Fugitive Mamoru-kun!

433
